&lt;h4&gt;Role Summary&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a Senior Power Electronics Engineer to lead the design and integration of high-power (&amp;gt;10 kW) power conversion hardware for aerospace motion and electrical systems. You will own key power-stage architecture decisions, drive prototype bring-up and verification, and partner with controls, firmware, mechanical, and manufacturing teams to deliver flight- and mission-ready hardware.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and design high-power converters/inverters (&amp;gt;10 kW) for aerospace electrical and motion control products, balancing efficiency, power density, and reliability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Select and apply Si, SiC, and/or GaN power devices (as appropriate) and design gate-drive, controller, feedback stability, magnetic components including power inductors and transformers, sensing, and protection (short-circuit, overcurrent, over/undervoltage, thermal, desaturation)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design topologies and the power stage (DC bus, precharge/discharge, snubbers/clamps, current sensing, filtering) and define safe operating envelopes and derating at given environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive thermal design with mechanical engineering (heatsinks, cold plates, airflow/liquid cooling) and validate junction-to-ambient performance including loss breakdown, thermal analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own EMI/EMC strategy for aerospace environments: grounding, shielding, layout constraints,&amp;nbsp;conducted/radiated mitigation, filter design, and test readiness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead schematic capture and review PCB layout for low-inductance, high-current/high-voltage design; ensure creepage/clearance, isolation, and safety best practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and execute prototype bring-up and high-power lab testing with safe procedures; debug failures and perform root-cause analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define verification plans and acceptance criteria and produce clear, review-ready test reports and evidence packages; support supplier/parts selection and DFM/DFT as designs transition to manufacturing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you need:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years (or equivalent depth) in power electronics design and product development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with power converter/inverter topologies, architecture, device selection, gate-drive design, controller selection, feedback gain, stability margin, protection, and high-voltage, high-current PCB/layout practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on bring-up and debug experience with high-power hardware (safe lab practices, oscilloscopes, HV differential probes, current probes, power analyzers, network/stability analyzers)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to take designs from concept through prototype, verification, and production readiness with clear documentatio

